# ESP32 DALI Tester (TFT UI + Encoder + Bus Monitor)

A compact, hands-on DALI tool built around an ESP32 with a 2.2" ILI9341 TFT and a rotary encoder. It can send DALI commands, scan devices, commission / change short addresses, 
clone key configuration values, reset device config, and monitor bus traffic.

> Note on provenance:  
> The firmware was created using AI-assisted “vibe coding” (with human iteration and testing).  
> The PCB / hardware wiring & integration were designed and built by hand.
> Current FW version (1.3.6) only allows for DALI1 and a few DALI2 devices (not all sensors are found).
> Please understand that the DALI bus may not be isolated from mains voltage! Do not use the internal power supply if there is allready voltage on the bus!
  If you are using the internal power supply, the DALI bus is not fully isolated! If you use an external supply, the tool is fully isolated.
  The internal power supply should be able to output 150mA, so it is not capable to supply a whole set of 64 devices, i tested it with more than 10 devices.

---

# Features

- TFT UI (ILI9341, 320×240) with header/footer and a scrollable home menu
- Rotary encoder navigation
  - Rotate: navigate lists / change values
  - Short click: select / execute
  - Long press (≥ 700 ms): back
  - Looong press (≥ 8000 ms): easteregg
- DALI Master (via `qqqlab/DALI-Lighting-Interface` / `qqqDALI`)
  - Send common commands (ON/OFF/MIN/MAX)
  - Query status, levels, device type
- Commissioning / addressing
  - Commission all devices
  - Commission unaddressed devices
  - Change short address (initialize → program → verify → terminate)
- Clone configuration
  - Capture and apply: max/min level, power-on level, system-failure level, fade time, fade rate
- Reset config (treats NO_REPLY as success, useful for some drivers)
- Bus Monitor
  - Displays decoded forward frames (address+data) and backward replies
  - Live mode + freeze/scroll mode

---

# Hardware

Core components
- ESP32 (DevKit style)
- ILI9341 2.2" SPI TFT (Adafruit compatible)
- Rotary encoder with push button
- DALI interface hardware (tested with Waveshare Pico-DALI2 and a Tridonic DALI USB “mouse” for generating traffic)
                           
---

# Firmware / Libraries

- Arduino framework on ESP32
- Display:
  - `Adafruit_GFX`
  - `Adafruit_ILI9341`
- DALI:
  - `qqqlab/DALI-Lighting-Interface` (`qqqDALI`)

The DALI timing is driven by a periodic ESP32 hardware timer ISR calling `dali.timer()`.

---

# Building

PlatformIO
1. Install VS Code + PlatformIO
2. Clone this repository
3. Open the folder in VS Code
4. Build and upload:
   - `PlatformIO: Build`
   - `PlatformIO: Upload`
5. Monitor serial output:
   - `PlatformIO: Monitor` (115200 baud)


---

# Project Status

This is an actively iterated DIY project. Expect occasional breaking changes while improving UI, decoding, or hardware compatibility.

